definition:
A man of the tribe of Judah living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at 1Ch.4.3; 
 son of: Hur (H2354); 
 brother of: Uri (H0221), Shobal (H7732H), Salma (H8007H), Hareph (H2780), Jezreel (H3157J), Idbash (H3031), Hazzelelponi (H6753), Penuel (H6439H) and Ezer (H5829) 
 § Ishma = "desolation"
 a Judaite descended from Hur
